{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:50:05.494Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branching creates parallel lines of development; merging combines them back. Agent teams branch to experiment with new prompts, tool sets, or model upgrades while keeping main stable \u2014 then merge after eval gates pass."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Git branching and merging workflow: feature branch, hotfix branch, and three merge strategies"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A branch is a movable pointer to a commit. "}, {"type": "text", "text": "main", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (or "}, {"type": "text", "text": "master", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") typically holds production-ready code. Feature branches like "}, {"type": "text", "text": "feat/reasoning-prompt-v2", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " diverge, accumulate commits, and merge via merge commit, squash, or rebase."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git checkout -b feat/tool-approval-flow\n# edit prompts and handlers\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"Add human-in-the-loop approval before delete tool\"\ngit checkout main\ngit merge feat/tool-approval-flow"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Running unreleased agent behavior in production risks bad tool calls. Branching isolates risky changes: eval runs on the branch; main stays deployable until merge approval."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Isolation", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 experiments do not block hotfixes on main"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Parallel work", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 multiple prompt iterations simultaneously"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reviewable units", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 one branch often maps to one PR"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rollback clarity", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 revert merge commit to undo feature"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge conflicts", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 same prompt file edited on two branches"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Long-lived branches", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 drift from main increases conflict cost"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebase risks", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 rewriting shared branch history confuses collaborators"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branch proliferation", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 stale experiment branches clutter remotes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Create and publish branch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git switch -c experiment/gpt4o-mini-tools\ngit push -u origin experiment/gpt4o-mini-tools"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge strategies"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merge commit preserves full branch history. Squash merge collapses branch commits into one on main \u2014 cleaner history for noisy WIP commits. Rebase replays commits atop main for linear history \u2014 use only on local/unshared branches."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Resolving conflicts"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "git switch main\ngit pull\ngit merge feat/new-system-prompt\n# CONFLICT in prompts/system.md\n# edit file, remove <<<<<<< markers\ngit add prompts/system.md\ngit commit"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For agent repos, conflicts in prompt files need human judgment \u2014 do not blindly accept one side; re-run evals after resolution."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use it"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Short-lived feature branches", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " per agent capability or prompt change"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Release branches", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (release/1.2) for stabilization before tag"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hotfix branches", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " off main for urgent tool safety patch"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Avoid", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " committing directly to main in team settings"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-world example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branch feat/rag-v2 updates retrieval prompt and chunk size. Daily merges from main keep it current. Eval harness on CI must beat baseline F1. Squash merge to main after two approvals; tag v1.8.0; deploy agent worker image with that SHA."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Merging without pulling latest main", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 surprises at merge time"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebasing public branches", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 forces collaborators to reset"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Resolving conflicts without re-running evals", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 silent prompt corruption"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Never deleting merged branches", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 remote clutter"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rebase or merge main into feature branch frequently"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One concern per branch when possible"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Delete remote branch after merge"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Document eval results in PR before merge"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use protected main \u2014 merge only via PR"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branches are alternate timelines; merging is choosing how two futures combine into one \u2014 like merging two draft agent prompts after human review."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Branch to isolate agent experiments; merge after validation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Understand merge commit vs squash vs rebase trade-offs"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Resolve prompt/config conflicts carefully; re-run evals"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keep branches short-lived and synced with main"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Protect main; avoid direct commits in shared repos"}]}]}]}]}}